UserConfLite

A sqlite solution to user configure

XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
------------------------------------------------------------

Archived in key-value way.

Ex:

int main(int, char**)[userconflite.cpp:90]: View.Chroma => 2
int main(int, char**)[userconflite.cpp:90]: View.Graymap => 3
int main(int, char**)[userconflite.cpp:90]: View.QRotate => 0
int main(int, char**)[userconflite.cpp:90]: View.Render => 3
int main(int, char**)[userconflite.cpp:90]: View.RotationX => 270
int main(int, char**)[userconflite.cpp:90]: View.RotationY => 0
int main(int, char**)[userconflite.cpp:90]: View.RotationZ => 270
int main(int, char**)[userconflite.cpp:90]: View.Vision => 0
int main(int, char**)[userconflite.cpp:90]: View.Zoom => 1

For a fresh setup system, initiate the configure db with

    sqlite3 UserConf.db3x < init_db.sql

Note:

    Uncommenting several lines in init_db.sql might be nessesary.

Build a initial demo with

    g++ `pkg-config --cflags --libs sqlite3` userconflite.cpp -o userconflite

Note:

    libsqliete3-devel or libsqliete3-dev is needed, which depends on you Linux box.

UserConf db is generated from init_db.sql, the following guys are generated by
different version of sqlite.

# file UserConf.*
UserConf.db2x: SQLite 2.x database
UserConf.db3x: SQLite 3.x database

Further Ex:
Work as a ConfigManage module

/* 
 * +-----+ update sys config   +----------------+
 * | DES +---------<<CGI>>---->+                |
 * | /   |                     | config.db/sys  |
 * | ENG +----<<USB/TERM>>---->+                |
 * +-----+                     +--+-------------+
 *                                | reset with config.db/sys
 *                                V
 *     /-----+             +----------------+    customize  +------+
 *    | DEV  |   configure |                +<--<<IFACE>>---+      |
 *    |      |<------------| config.db/user |               | User |
 *     +--+--/             |                +<---<<IFACE>>--+      |
 *        |                +----------------+    reset op   +------+
 *        |                                                    A
 *        +----------------------------------------------------+
 *                         effect, response, image, blah
 */

